
# üéì University Admin Panel - MERN Stack Dashboard

This project is a **comprehensive Admin Dashboard** for managing academic data at a university. Built using the **MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js)**, the dashboard allows administrators to view and manage data related to **MoUs, courses, training participants, and sector-specific programs**.

---

## üöÄ Features

The dashboard consists of **6 main interactive buttons**, each rendering structured and filtered information from the backend:

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ No. of MoUs
- Displays a list of all **MoUs** (Memorandums of Understanding) signed by the university.

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Ongoing Courses
- Shows all **ongoing courses** currently being conducted at the university.

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ MoU Activities under Schools
- Displays a list of **schools** with at least one signed MoU.
- On clicking a school, it reveals all MoUs signed under that particular school.

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Total Number of Courses
- Lists all **completed courses** conducted by the university.

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Total Number of Participants Trained
- Shows a list of all **participants** who have either completed or are undergoing a course.

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Sector-Specific Training Programs
- Displays a list of **fields/sectors** (e.g., Cybersecurity, AI, etc.) on which training is offered.
- Clicking on a sector reveals all **courses** conducted in that specific field.

